 

CELTIC star Anthony Stokes and his missus are expecting their second child.
His long-term partner Debbie Lawlor announced that her new arrival is due in October.
The 27-year-old revealed on social media that she broke the news to the couple’s son Bobby by reading him kids’ book There’s A House Inside My Mummy.
She wrote on Instagram: “It’s his latest bedtime story.
“We’re all excited – he can’t wait to be a big bro.”
 

Irish star Stokes, 26, and Debbie have been together for nine years.
Their first son is now three years old.
The couple first got together as teenagers in Dublin when they both went to different high schools.
